Question.Text: A 74-Year-Old Man from Japan With a history of fever, joint pain, headache, and nausea over the past 5 days. He has a history of cerebral infarction without neurological sequelae, hypertension and ulcerative colitis. He is taking antiplatelet, and antihypertensive medicine and subcutaneous injection of the TNF-alpha Blocker adalimumab once every 2 weeks.
